.TH GAT-LIST 1 "2026-06-04" "gat 0.3.0" "gat Manual"
.SH NAME
gat-list \- list registered worktrees with status and change stats
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B gat list
.RB [ \-\-format
.IR text|json ]
.RB [ \-\-fast ]
.br
.B gat ls
.RI [ ... ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Shows every worktree with its branch, state
.RI ( primary / detached / dirty / merged / locked / missing ),
short HEAD, a change summary, idle time, and description. In full mode it
computes per-worktree status in parallel across worker threads. The
.I @
marker indicates the current worktree.
.PP
The
.I Changes
column is rendered as
.IR <files>f " " +<insertions> " " \-<deletions> ,
where files counts staged, unstaged, and untracked paths, and
insertions/deletions come from
.BR "git diff \-\-shortstat HEAD" .
The
.I Idle
column shows days since the worktree was last accessed, falling back to
filesystem modification time when no usage is tracked.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-fast
Skip per-worktree dirty/merged/diff checks for instant output.
.TP
.B \-\-watch
Continuously re-render (delegates to
.BR gat\-watch (1)).
.TP
.BI \-\-format " text|json"
Output format.
.SH "JSON FIELDS"
.IR path ", " branch ", " head ", " primary ", " detached ", " dirty ", " merged ", "
.IR changed_files ", " insertions ", " deletions ", " locked ", " prunable ", "
.IR idle_days ", " description .
.SH EXAMPLES
.RS
.EX
gat list
gat ls \-\-fast
gat list \-\-json | jq '.[] | select(.dirty)'
.EE
.RE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR gat (1),
.BR gat\-watch (1),
.BR gat\-search (1)
